<h4 id="ising">Ising</h4>
<ol>
  <li>\(E(\mathrm{x} ; J, H)=-\left[\frac{1}{2} \sum_{m, n} J_{m n} x_{m} x_{n}+\sum_{n}
H x_{n}\right]\)
    <ul>
      <li>The coupling between neighbouring spins is J. we define $J_{mn}=J$ if m and n
are neighbours and $J_{mn}=0$ otherwise.</li>
      <li>H is the applied field</li>
      <li>We have included the factor of $\frac{1}{2}$, because each pair is counted
twice in the first sum, once as (m,n) and once as (n,m)</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>The probability that the state is x is: <br />
\(P(\mathrm{x} | \beta, J, H)=\frac{1}{Z(\beta, J, H)} \exp [-\beta E(\mathrm{x} ;
J, H)]\)
    <ul>
      <li>
\[Z(\beta, J, H) \equiv \sum_{\mathbf{x}} \exp [-\beta E(\mathbf{x} ; J, H)]\]
      </li>
      <li>\(\beta=1 / k_{\mathrm{B}} T\), \(k_B\) is a Boltzmannâ€™s constant</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ol>

